INSERT INTO sat_tests (title, description, test_type, difficulty, length, section, is_official, time_limit_minutes, questions) VALUES ('OpenSAT Math - Normal Set 2','Official-style SAT Math practice (Normal) from OpenSAT — image-free questions only.','math','normal','medium','math',true,38,'[{"id": "opensat-math-mcq-69", "text": "x plus 2 y equals 6\nx minus 2 y equals 4\nThe solution to the given system of equations is left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis. What is the value of x?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["2.5", "5", "6", "10"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. Adding the first equation to the second equation in the given system yields left parenthesis x plus 2 y right parenthesis plus left parenthesis x minus 2 y right parenthesis equals 6 plus 4, or left parenthesis x plus x right parenthesis plus left parenthesis 2 y minus 2 y right parenthesis equals 10. Combining like terms in this equation yields 2 x equals 10. Dividing both sides of this equation by 2 yields x equals 5. Thus, the value of x is 5.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the value of 2 x, not x."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-75", "text": "A moving truck can tow a trailer if the combined weight of the trailer and the boxes it contains is no more than 4,600 pounds. What is the maximum number of boxes this truck can tow in a trailer with a weight of 500 pounds if each box weighs 120 pounds?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["34", "35", "38", "39"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. It\u2019s given that the truck can tow a trailer if the combined weight of the trailer and the boxes it contains is no more than 4,600 pounds. If the trailer has a weight of 500 pounds and each box weighs 120 pounds, the expression 500 plus 120 b, where b is the number of boxes, gives the combined weight of the trailer and the boxes. Since the combined weight must be no more than 4,600 pounds, the possible numbers of boxes the truck can tow are given by the inequality 500 plus 120 b less than or equals 4,600. Subtracting 500 from both sides of this inequality yields 120 b less than or equals 4,100. Dividing both sides of this inequality by 120 yields b less than or equals StartFraction 205 Over 6 EndFraction, or b is less than or equal to approximately 34.17. Since the number of boxes, b, must be a whole number, the maximum number of boxes the truck can tow is the greatest whole number less than 34.17, which is 34.\nChoice B is incorrect. Towing the trailer and 35 boxes would yield a combined weight of 4,700 pounds, which is greater than 4,600 pounds.\nChoice C is incorrect. Towing the trailer and 38 boxes would yield a combined weight of 5,060 pounds, which is greater than 4,600 pounds.\nChoice D is incorrect. Towing the trailer and 39 boxes would yield a combined weight of 5,180 pounds, which is greater than 4,600 pounds."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-80", "text": "Based on a random sample from a population, a researcher estimated that the mean value of a certain variable for the population is 20.5, with an associated margin of error of 1. Which of the following is the most appropriate conclusion?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["It is plausible that the actual mean value of the variable for the population is between 19.5 and 21.5.", "It is not possible that the mean value of the variable for the population is less than 19.5 or greater than 21.5.", "Every value of the variable in the population is between 19.5 and 21.5.", "The mean value of the variable for the population is 20.5."], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. It''s given that based on a random sample from a population, the estimated mean value for a certain variable for the population is 20.5, with an associated margin of error of 1. This means that it is plausible that the actual mean value of the variable for the population is between 20.5 minus 1 and 20.5 plus 1. Therefore, the most appropriate conclusion is that it is plausible that the actual mean value of the variable for the population is between 19.5 and 21.5.\nChoice B is incorrect. The estimated mean value and associated margin of error describe only plausible values, not all the possible values, for the actual mean value of the variable, so this is not an appropriate conclusion.\nChoice C is incorrect. The estimated mean value and associated margin of error describe only plausible values for the actual mean value of the variable, not all the possible values of the variable, so this is not an appropriate conclusion.\nChoice D is incorrect. Since 20.5 is the estimated mean value of the variable based on a random sample, the actual mean value of the variable may not be exactly 20.5. Therefore, this is not an appropriate conclusion."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-83", "text": "In the table above, Melissa recorded the price of one gallon of regular gas from five different local gas stations on the same day. What is the median of the gas prices Melissa recorded?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["$3.679", "$3.689", "$3.699", "$3.729"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. The median of a data set is the middle value when the data is in ascending or descending order. In ascending order, the gas prices are $3.609, $3.679, $3.699, $3.729, and $3.729. The middle number of this list is 3.699, so it follows that $3.699 is the median gas price.Choice A is incorrect. When the gas prices are listed in ascending order, this value isn\u2019t the middle number. Choice B is incorrect. This value represents the mean gas price. Choice D is incorrect. This value represents both the mode and the maximum gas price."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-84", "text": "The function h is defined by h left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 4 x plus 28. The graph of y equals h left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the xy-plane has an x-intercept at left parenthesis a comma 0 right parenthesis and a y-intercept at left parenthesis 0 comma b right parenthesis, where a and b are constants. What is the value of a plus b?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["21", "28", "32", "35"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. The x-intercept of a graph in the xy-plane is the point on the graph where y equals 0. It''s given that function h is defined by h left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 4 x plus 28. Therefore, the equation representing the graph of y equals h left parenthesis x right parenthesis is y equals 4 x plus 28. Substituting 0 for y in the equation y equals 4 x plus 28 yields 0 equals 4 x plus 28. Subtracting 28 from both sides of this equation yields negative 28 equals 4 x. Dividing both sides of this equation by 4 yields negative 7 equals x. Therefore, the x-intercept of the graph of y equals h left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the xy-plane is left parenthesis negative 7 comma 0 right parenthesis. It''s given that the x-intercept of the graph of y equals h left parenthesis x right parenthesis is left parenthesis a comma 0 right parenthesis. Therefore, a equals negative 7. The y-intercept of a graph in the xy-plane is the point on the graph where x equals 0. Substituting 0 for x in the equation y equals 4 x plus 28 yields y equals 4 left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis plus 28, or y equals 28. Therefore, the y-intercept of the graph of y equals h left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the xy-plane is left parenthesis 0 comma 28 right parenthesis. It''s given that the y-intercept of the graph of y equals h left parenthesis x right parenthesis is left parenthesis 0 comma b right parenthesis. Therefore, b equals 28. If a equals negative 7 and b equals 28, then the value of a plus b is negative 7 plus 28, or 21.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the value of b, not a plus b.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the value of negative a plus b, not a plus b."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-88", "text": "In a bag, there are 7 red, 4 white, 33 blue, and 33 yellow cubes. If one of these cubes is selected at random, what is the probability of selecting a cube that is neither blue nor yellow?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["six sevenths", "seven elevenths", "one third", "one seventh"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. It\u2019s given that there are 7 red, 4 white, 33 blue, and 33 yellow cubes in the bag. Therefore, there are a total of 7 plus 4 plus 33 plus 33, or 77, cubes in the bag. If the cube is neither blue nor yellow, then it must be either red or white. Therefore, the probability of selecting a cube that is neither blue nor yellow is equivalent to the probability of selecting a cube that is either red or white. If one of these cubes is selected at random, the probability of selecting a cube that is either red or white is equal to the sum of the number of red cubes and white cubes divided by the total number of cubes in the bag. There are 7 red cubes, 4 white cubes, and 77 total cubes in the bag. Therefore, the probability of selecting a red or white cube is StartFraction 7 plus 4 Over 77 EndFraction, which is equivalent to StartFraction 11 Over 77 EndFraction, or one seventh. Thus, if one cube is selected at random, the probability of selecting a cube that is neither blue nor yellow is one seventh.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the probability of selecting a cube that is either blue or yellow, rather than the probability of selecting a cube that is neither blue nor yellow.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-91", "text": "A model predicts that the population of Springfield was 15,000 in 2005. The model also predicts that each year for the next 5 years, the population p increased by 4 percent sign of the previous year''s population. Which equation best represents this model, where x is the number of years after 2005, for x less than or equals 5?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["p equals 0.96 left parenthesis 15,000 right parenthesis Superscript x", "p equals 1.04 left parenthesis 15,000 right parenthesis Superscript x", "p equals 15,000 left parenthesis 0.96 right parenthesis Superscript x", "p equals 15,000 left parenthesis 1.04 right parenthesis Superscript x"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. It''s given that a model predicts the population of Springfield in 2005 was 15,000. The model also predicts that each year for the next 5 years, the population increased by 4 percent sign of the previous year''s population. The predicted population in one of these years can be found by multiplying the predicted population from the previous year by 1.04. Since the predicted population in 2005 was 15,000, the predicted population 1 year later is 15,000 left parenthesis 1.04 right parenthesis. The predicted population 2 years later is this value times 1.04, which is 15,000 left parenthesis 1.04 right parenthesis left parenthesis 1.04 right parenthesis, or 15,000 left parenthesis 1.04 right parenthesis squared. The predicted population 3 years later is this value times 1.04, or 15,000 left parenthesis 1.04 right parenthesis cubed. More generally, the predicted population, p, x years after 2005 is represented by the equation p equals 15,000 left parenthesis 1.04 right parenthesis Superscript x. \nChoice A is incorrect. Substituting 0 for x in this equation indicates the predicted population in 2005 was 0.96 rather than 15,000.\nChoice B is incorrect. Substituting 0 for x in this equation indicates the predicted population in 2005 was 1.04 rather than 15,000.\nChoice C is incorrect. This equation indicates the predicted population is decreasing, rather than increasing, by 4 percent sign each year."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-93", "text": "*{stroke-linecap:butt;stroke-linejoin:round;}\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\nClockwise from top left, the 3 lines are labeled m, r, and s.\nLine m intersects both line r and line s.\nAt the intersection of line m and line r, 1 angle is labeled clockwise from top left as follows:\n\nTop right: x\u00b0\n\nAt the intersection of line m and line s, 1 angle is labeled clockwise from top left as follows:\n\nBottom right: y\u00b0\n\nA note indicates the figure is not drawn to scale.\n\nIn the figure shown, lines r and s are parallel, and line m intersects both lines. If y less than 65, which of the following must be true?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["x less than 115", "x greater than 115", "x plus y less than 180", "x plus y greater than 180"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. In the figure shown, the angle measuring y degree is congruent to its vertical angle formed by lines s and m, so the measure of the vertical angle is also y degree. The vertical angle forms a same-side interior angle pair with the angle measuring x degree. It''s given that lines r and s are parallel. Therefore, same-side interior angles in the figure are supplementary, which means the sum of the measure of the vertical angle and the measure of the angle measuring x degree is 180 degree, or x plus y equals 180. Subtracting x from both sides of this equation yields y equals 180 minus x. Substituting 180 minus x for y in the inequality y less than 65 yields 180 minus x less than 65. Adding x to both sides of this inequality yields 180 less than 65 plus x. Subtracting 65 from both sides of this inequality yields 115 less than x, or x greater than 115. Thus, if y less than 65, it must be true that x greater than 115.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect. x plus y must be equal to, not less than, 180.\nChoice D is incorrect. x plus y must be equal to, not greater than, 180."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-95", "text": "The area A, in square centimeters, of a rectangular painting can be represented by the expression w left parenthesis w plus 29 right parenthesis, where w is the width, in centimeters, of the painting. Which expression represents the length, in centimeters, of the painting?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["w", "29", "left parenthesis w plus 29 right parenthesis", "w left parenthesis w plus 29 right parenthesis"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. It''s given that the expression w left parenthesis w plus 29 right parenthesis represents the area, in square centimeters, of a rectangular painting, where w is the width, in centimeters, of the painting. The area of a rectangle can be calculated by multiplying its length by its width. It follows that the length, in centimeters, of the painting is represented by the expression left parenthesis w plus 29 right parenthesis.\nChoice A is incorrect. This expression represents the width, in centimeters, of the painting, not its length, in centimeters.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the difference between the length, in centimeters, and the width, in centimeters, of the painting, not its length, in centimeters.\nChoice D is incorrect. This expression represents the area, in square centimeters, of the painting, not its length, in centimeters."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-96", "text": "Time (years)\nTotal amount (dollars)\n\n0\n604.00\n\n1\n606.42\n\n2\n608.84\n\nRosa opened a savings account at a bank. The table shows the exponential relationship between the time t, in years, since Rosa opened the account and the total amount n, in dollars, in the account. If Rosa made no additional deposits or withdrawals, which of the following equations best represents the relationship between t and n?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["|n equals left parenthesis 1 plus 604 right parenthesis Superscript t|", "|n equals left parenthesis 1 plus 0.004 right parenthesis Superscript t|", "|n equals 604 left parenthesis 1 plus 0.004 right parenthesis Superscript t|", "|n equals 0.004 left parenthesis 1 plus 604 right parenthesis Superscript t|"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. It\u2019s given that the relationship between t and n is exponential. The table shows that the value of n increases as the value of t increases. Therefore, the relationship between t and n can be represented by an increasing exponential equation of the form n equals a left parenthesis 1 plus b right parenthesis Superscript t, where a and b are positive constants. The table shows that when t equals 0, n equals 604. Substituting 0 for t and 604 for n in the equation n equals a left parenthesis 1 plus b right parenthesis Superscript t yields 604 equals a left parenthesis 1 plus b right parenthesis Superscript 0, which is equivalent to 604 equals a left parenthesis 1 right parenthesis, or 604 equals a. Substituting 604 for a in the equation n equals a left parenthesis 1 plus b right parenthesis Superscript t yields n equals 604 left parenthesis 1 plus b right parenthesis Superscript t. The table also shows that when t equals 1, n equals 606.42. Substituting 1 for t and 606.42 for n in the equation n equals 604 left parenthesis 1 plus b right parenthesis Superscript t yields 606.42 equals 604 left parenthesis 1 plus b right parenthesis Superscript 1, or 606.42 equals 604 left parenthesis 1 plus b right parenthesis. Dividing both sides of this equation by 604 yields approximately 1.004 equals 1 plus b. Subtracting 1 from both sides of this equation yields that the value of b is approximately 0.004. Substituting 0.004 for b in the equation n equals 604 left parenthesis 1 plus b right parenthesis Superscript t yields n equals 604 left parenthesis 1 plus 0.004 right parenthesis Superscript t. Therefore, of the choices, choice C best represents the relationship between t and n.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-98", "text": "f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus 5 right parenthesis left parenthesis x minus 4 right parenthesis\nThe function f is given. Which table of values represents y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis minus 3?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["x\ny\n\nnegative 6\nnegative 9\n\nnegative 5\nnegative 8\n\n4\n1", "x\ny\n\nnegative 6\nnegative 3\n\nnegative 5\nnegative 3\n\n4\nnegative 3", "x\ny\n\nnegative 6\nnegative 3\n\nnegative 5\nnegative 2\n\n4\n7", "x\ny\n\nnegative 6\n3\n\nnegative 5\n3\n\n4\n3"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. It\u2019s given that f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus 5 right parenthesis left parenthesis x minus 4 right parenthesis and y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis minus 3. Substituting left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus 5 right parenthesis left parenthesis x minus 4 right parenthesis for f left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the equation y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis minus 3 yields y equals left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus 5 right parenthesis left parenthesis x minus 4 right parenthesis minus 3. Substituting negative 6 for x in this equation yields y equals left parenthesis negative 6 plus 6 right parenthesis left parenthesis negative 6 plus 5 right parenthesis left parenthesis negative 6 minus 4 right parenthesis minus 3, or y equals negative 3. Substituting negative 5 for x in the equation y equals left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus 5 right parenthesis left parenthesis x minus 4 right parenthesis minus 3 yields y equals left parenthesis negative 5 plus 6 right parenthesis left parenthesis negative 5 plus 5 right parenthesis left parenthesis negative 5 minus 4 right parenthesis minus 3, or y equals negative 3. Substituting 4 for x in the equation y equals left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus 5 right parenthesis left parenthesis x minus 4 right parenthesis minus 3 yields y equals left parenthesis 4 plus 6 right parenthesis left parenthesis 4 plus 5 right parenthesis left parenthesis 4 minus 4 right parenthesis minus 3, or y equals negative 3. Therefore, when x equals negative 6 then y equals negative 3, when x equals negative 5 then y equals negative 3, and when x equals 4 then y equals negative 3. Thus, the table of values in choice B represents y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis minus 3.\nChoice A is incorrect. This table represents y equals x minus 3 rather than y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis minus 3.\nChoice C is incorrect. This table represents y equals x plus 3 rather than y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis minus 3.\nChoice D is incorrect. This table represents y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis plus 3 rather than y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis minus 3."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-99", "text": "x plus 3 equals minus 2 y plus 5\nx minus 3 equals 2 y plus 7\nThe solution to the given system of equations is left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis. What is the value of 2 x?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["negative 2", "6", "12", "24"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. Adding the second equation in the given system to the first equation in the given system yields left parenthesis x plus 3 right parenthesis plus left parenthesis x minus 3 right parenthesis equals left parenthesis minus 2 y plus 5 right parenthesis plus left parenthesis 2 y plus 7 right parenthesis. Adding like terms in this equation yields 2 x equals 12. Thus, the value of 2 x is 12.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the value of y, not 2 x.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the value of x, not 2 x.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-100", "text": "A study was done on the weights of different types of fish in a pond. A random sample of fish were caught and marked in order to ensure that none were weighed more than once. The sample contained 150 largemouth bass, of which 30% weighed more than 2 pounds. Which of the following conclusions is best supported by the sample data?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["The majority of all fish in the pond weigh less than 2 pounds.", "The average weight of all fish in the pond is approximately 2 pounds.", "Approximately 30% of all fish in the pond weigh more than 2 pounds.", "Approximately 30% of all largemouth bass in the pond weigh more than 2 pounds."], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. The sample of 150 largemouth bass was selected at random from all the largemouth bass in the pond, and since 30% of the fish in the sample weighed more than 2 pounds, it can be concluded that approximately 30% of all largemouth bass in the pond weigh more than 2 pounds.Choices A, B, and C are incorrect. Since the sample contained 150 largemouth bass, of which 30% weighed more than 2 pounds, this result can be generalized only to largemouth bass in the pond, not to all fish in the pond."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-101", "text": "The function p is defined by p left parenthesis n right parenthesis equals 7 n cubed. What is the value of n when p left parenthesis n right parenthesis is equal to 56?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["2", "eight thirds", "7", "8"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. It''s given that p left parenthesis n right parenthesis equals 7 n cubed. Substituting 56 for p left parenthesis n right parenthesis in this equation yields 56 equals 7 n cubed. Dividing each side of this equation by 7 yields 8 equals n cubed. Taking the cube root of each side of this equation yields 2 equals n. Therefore, when p left parenthesis n right parenthesis is equal to 56, the value of n is 2.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-110", "text": "Triangle upper F upper G upper H is similar to triangle upper J upper K upper L, where angle upper F corresponds to angle upper J and angles upper G and upper K are right angles. If sine left parenthesis upper F right parenthesis equals StartFraction 308 Over 317 EndFraction, what is the value of sine left parenthesis upper J right parenthesis?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["StartFraction 75 Over 317 EndFraction", "StartFraction 308 Over 317 EndFraction", "StartFraction 317 Over 308 EndFraction", "StartFraction 317 Over 75 EndFraction"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. If two triangles are similar, then their corresponding angles are congruent. It''s given that right triangle upper F upper G upper H is similar to right triangle upper J upper K upper L and angle upper F corresponds to angle upper J. It follows that angle upper F is congruent to angle upper J and, therefore, the measure of angle upper F is equal to the measure of angle upper J. The sine ratios of angles of equal measure are equal. Since the measure of angle upper F is equal to the measure of angle upper J, sine left parenthesis upper F right parenthesis equals sine left parenthesis upper J right parenthesis. It''s given that sine left parenthesis upper F right parenthesis equals StartFraction 308 Over 317 EndFraction. Therefore, sine left parenthesis upper J right parenthesis is StartFraction 308 Over 317 EndFraction.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the value of cosine left parenthesis upper J right parenthesis, not the value of sine left parenthesis upper J right parenthesis.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the reciprocal of the value of sine left parenthesis upper J right parenthesis, not the value of sine left parenthesis upper J right parenthesis.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the reciprocal of the value of cosine left parenthesis upper J right parenthesis, not the value of sine left parenthesis upper J right parenthesis."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-113", "text": "A sample consisting of 720 adults who own televisions was selected at random for a study. Based on the sample, it is estimated that 32 percent sign of all adul