 comma 0 right parenthesis is given as a choice.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-220", "text": "The measure of angle upper R is StartFraction 2 pi Over 3 EndFraction radians. The measure of angle upper T is StartFraction 5 pi Over 12 EndFraction radians greater than the measure of angle upper R. What is the measure of angle upper T, in degrees?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["75", "120", "195", "390"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. It\u2019s given that the measure of angle upper R is StartFraction 2 pi Over 3 EndFraction radians, and the measure of angle upper T is StartFraction 5 pi Over 12 EndFraction radians greater than the measure of angle upper R. Therefore, the measure of angle upper T is equal to StartFraction 2 pi Over 3 EndFraction plus StartFraction 5 pi Over 12 EndFraction radians. Multiplying StartFraction 2 pi Over 3 EndFraction by four fourths to get a common denominator with StartFraction 5 pi Over 12 EndFraction yields StartFraction 8 pi Over 12 EndFraction. Therefore, StartFraction 2 pi Over 3 EndFraction plus StartFraction 5 pi Over 12 EndFraction is equivalent to StartFraction 8 pi Over 12 EndFraction plus StartFraction 5 pi Over 12 EndFraction, or StartFraction 13 pi Over 12 EndFraction. Therefore, the measure of angle upper T is StartFraction 13 pi Over 12 EndFraction radians. The measure of angle upper T, in degrees, can be found by multiplying its measure, in radians, by StartFraction 180 Over pi EndFraction. This yields StartFraction 13 pi Over 12 EndFraction times StartFraction 180 Over pi EndFraction, which is equivalent to 195 degrees. Therefore, the measure of angle upper T is 195 degrees.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the number of degrees that the measure of angle upper T is greater than the measure of angle upper R.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the measure of angle upper R, in degrees.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-223", "text": "The function f is defined by f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 7 x minus 84. What is the x-intercept of the graph of y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the xy-plane?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["left parenthesis negative 12 comma 0 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis negative 7 comma 0 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis 7 comma 0 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis 12 comma 0 right parenthesis"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. The given function f is a linear function. Therefore, the graph of y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the xy-plane has one x-intercept at the point left parenthesis k comma 0 right parenthesis, where k is a constant. Substituting 0 for f left parenthesis x right parenthesis and k for x in the given function yields 0 equals 7 k minus 84. Adding 84 to both sides of this equation yields 84 equals 7 k. Dividing both sides of this equation by 7 yields 12 equals k. Therefore, the x-intercept of the graph of y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the xy-plane is left parenthesis 12 comma 0 right parenthesis.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-224", "text": "A company that provides whale-watching tours takes groups of 21 people at a time. The company\u2019s revenue is 80 dollars per adult and 60 dollars per child. If the company\u2019s revenue for one group consisting of adults and children was 1,440 dollars, how many people in the group were children?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["3", "9", "12", "18"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. Let x represent the number of children in a whale-watching tour group. Let y represent the number of adults in this group. Because it''s given that 21 people are in a group and the group consists of adults and children, it must be true that x plus y equals 21. Since the company''s revenue is 60 dollars per child, the total revenue from x children in this group was 60 x dollars. Since the company''s revenue is 80 dollars per adult, the total revenue from y adults in this group was 80 y dollars. Because it''s given that the total revenue for this group was 1,440 dollars, it must be true that 60 x plus 80 y equals 1,440. The equations x plus y equals 21 and 60 x plus 80 y equals 1,440 form a linear system of equations that can be solved to find the value of x, which represents the number of children in the group, using the elimination method. Multiplying both sides of the equation x plus y equals 21 by 80 yields 80 x plus 80 y equals 1,680. Subtracting 60 x plus 80 y equals 1,440 from 80 x plus 80 y equals 1,680 yields left parenthesis 80 x plus 80 y right parenthesis minus left parenthesis 60 x plus 80 y right parenthesis equals 1,680 minus 1,440, which is equivalent to 80 x minus 60 x plus 80 y minus 80 y equals 240, or 20 x equals 240. Dividing both sides of this equation by 20 yields x equals 12. Therefore, 12 people in the group were children.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the number of adults in the group, not the number of children in the group.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}]'::jsonb);
