t whales from the genus Eschrichtius travel 72 to 77 miles in the ocean each day during their migration. If one of these whales travels 72 miles each day for 16 days, then the whale travels 72 left parenthesis 16 right parenthesis miles total. If one of these whales travels 77 miles each day for 16 days, then the whale travels 77 left parenthesis 16 right parenthesis miles total. Therefore, the model estimates that in 16 days of its migration, a whale from the genus Eschrichtius could travel at least 72 left parenthesis 16 right parenthesis and at most 77 left parenthesis 16 right parenthesis miles total. Thus, the inequality left parenthesis 72 right parenthesis left parenthesis 16 right parenthesis less than or equals x less than or equals left parenthesis 77 right parenthesis left parenthesis 16 right parenthesis represents the estimated total number of miles, x, a whale from the genus Eschrichtius could travel in 16 days of its migration.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-258", "text": "Which expression is equivalent to RootIndex 7 StartRoot x Superscript 9 Baseline y Superscript 9 Baseline EndRoot, where x and y are positive?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["left parenthesis x y right parenthesis Superscript seven ninths", "left parenthesis x y right parenthesis Superscript nine sevenths", "left parenthesis x y right parenthesis Superscript 16", "left parenthesis x y right parenthesis Superscript 63"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. For positive values of a and b, a Superscript m Baseline b Superscript m Baseline equals left parenthesis a b right parenthesis Superscript m, RootIndex n StartRoot a EndRoot equals left parenthesis a right parenthesis Superscript StartFraction 1 Over n EndFra