h of arc upper Q upper R?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["24 pi", "48 pi", "72 pi", "96 pi"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. Since Line Segment upper P upper R and Line Segment upper Q upper S are diameters of the circle shown, Line Segment upper O upper S, Line Segment upper O upper R, Line Segment upper O upper P, and Line Segment upper O upper Q are radii of the circle and are therefore congruent. Since angle upper S upper O upper P and angle upper R upper O upper Q are vertical angles, they are congruent. Therefore, arc upper P upper S and arc upper Q upper R are formed by congruent radii and have the same angle measure, so they are congruent arcs. Similarly, angle upper S upper O upper R and angle upper P upper O upper Q are vertical angles, so they are congruent. Therefore, arc upper S upper R and arc upper P upper Q are formed by congruent radii and have the same angle measure, so they are congruent arcs. Let x represent the length of arc upper S upper R. Since arc upper S upper R and arc upper P upper Q are congruent arcs, the length of arc upper P upper Q can also be represented by x. It\u2019s given that the length of arc upper P upper S is twice the length of arc upper P upper Q. Therefore, the length of arc upper P upper S can be represented by the expression 2 x. Since arc upper P upper S and arc upper Q upper R are congruent arcs, the length of arc upper Q upper R can also be represented by 2 x. This gives the expression x plus x plus 2 x plus 2 x. Since it''s given that the circumference is 144 pi, the expression x plus x plus 2 x plus 2 x is equal to 144 pi. Thus x plus x plus 2 x plus 2 x equals 144 pi, or 6 x equals 144 pi. Dividing both sides of this equation by 6 yields x equals 24 pi. Therefore, the length of arc upper Q upper R is 2 left parenthesis 24 pi right parenthesis, or 48 pi.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the length of arc upper P upper Q, not arc upper Q upper R.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-381", "text": "StartFraction 1 Over 7 b EndFraction equals StartFraction 11 x Over y EndFraction\nThe given equation relates the positive numbers b, x, and y. Which equation correctly expresses x in terms of b and y?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["x equals StartFraction 7 b y Over 11 EndFraction", "x equals y minus 77 b", "x equals StartFraction y Over 77 b EndFraction", "x equals 77 b y"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. Multiplying each side of the given equation by y yields the equivalent equation StartFraction y Over 7 b EndFraction equals 11 x. Dividing each side of this equation by 11 yields StartFraction y Over 77 b EndFraction equals x, or x equals StartFraction y Over 77 b EndFraction.\nChoice A is incorrect. This equation is not equivalent to the given equation. \nChoice B is incorrect. This equation is not equivalent to the given equation. \nChoice D is incorrect. This equation is not equivalent to the given equation."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-391", "text": "A cube has an edge length of 41 inches. What is the volume, in cubic inches, of the cube?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["164", "1,681", "10,086", "68,921"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. The volume, upper V, of a cube can be found using the formula upper V equals s cubed, where s is the edge length of the cube. It''s given that a cube has an edge length of 41 inches. Substituting 41 inches for s in this equation yields upper V equals 41 cubed cubic inches, or upper V equals 68,921 cubic inches. Therefore, the volume of the cube is 68,921 cubic inches.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the perimeter, in inches, of the cube.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the area, in square inches, of a face of the cube.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the surface area, in square inches, of the cube."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-392", "text": "y equals minus one ninth x\ny equals one half x\nThe solution to the given system of equations is left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis. What is the value of x?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["negative 9", "negative 7", "0", "2"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. It''s given by the first equation in the system that y equals minus one ninth x. Substituting minus one ninth x for y in the second equation in the system yields minus one ninth x equals one half x. Multiplying the left-hand side of this equation by two halves and the right-hand side by nine ninths yields minus two eighteenths x equals nine eighteenths x. Adding two eighteenths x to both sides of this equation yields 0 equals StartFraction 11 Over 18 EndFraction x. Multiplying both sides of this equation by StartFraction 18 Over 11 EndFraction yields x equals 0.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors. \nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors. \nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-396", "text": "For the dot plot titled Class A:\n\nThe number line ranges from 1 to 7 in increments of 1.\nThe data for the dot plot are as follows:\n\n1: 1 dot\n2: 1 dot\n3: 3 dots\n4: 4 dots\n5: 5 dots\n6: 6 dots\n7: 7 dots\n\nFor the dot plot titled Class B:\n\nThe number line ranges from 14 to 20 in increments of 1.\nThe data for the dot plot are as follows:\n\n14: 1 dot\n15: 1 dot\n16: 3 dots\n17: 4 dots\n18: 5 dots\n19: 6 dots\n20: 7 dots\n\nEach of the dot plots shown represents the number of glue sticks brought in by each student for two classes, class A a