 incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-441", "text": "Which expression represents the result of increasing a positive quantity w by 43 percent sign?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["1.43 w", "0.57 w", "43 w", "0.43 w"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. The result of increasing a positive quantity w by x percent sign can be represented by the expression left parenthesis 1 plus StartFraction x Over 100 EndFraction right parenthesis w. Therefore, the result of increasing a positive quantity w by 43 percent sign can be found by substituting 43 for x in the expression left parenthesis 1 plus StartFraction x Over 100 EndFraction right parenthesis w, which gives left parenthesis 1 plus StartFraction 43 Over 100 EndFraction right parenthesis w, or 1.43 w. Thus, the expression 1.43 w represents the result of increasing a positive quantity w by 43 percent sign.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the result of decreasing a positive quantity w by 43 percent sign.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the result of increasing a positive quantity w by 4,200 percent sign.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the result of decreasing a positive quantity w by 57 percent sign."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-442", "text": "For the finale of a TV show, viewers could use either social media or a text message to vote for their favorite of two contestants. The contestant receiving more than 50% of the vote won. An estimated 10% of the viewers voted, and 30% of the votes were cast on social media. Contestant 2 earned 70% of the votes cast using social media and 40% of the votes cast using a text message. Based on this information, which of the following is an accurate conclusion?", "type": "multiple_choice",