ation has a positive slope, not a negative slope."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-451", "text": "In the xy-plane, line k passes through the points left parenthesis 0 comma negative 5 right parenthesis and left parenthesis 1 comma negative 1 right parenthesis. Which equation defines line k?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["y equals negative x plus one fourth", "y equals one fourth x minus 5", "y equals negative x plus 4", "y equals 4 x minus 5"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. An equation defining a line in the xy-plane can be written in the form y equals m x plus b, where m represents the slope and left parenthesis 0 comma b right parenthesis represents the y-intercept of the line. It\u2019s given that line k passes through the point left parenthesis 0 comma negative 5 right parenthesis; therefore, b equals negative 5. The slope, m, of a line can be found using any two points on the line, left parenthesis x 1 comma y 1 right parenthesis and left parenthesis x 2 comma y 2 right parenthesis, and the slope formula m equals StartFraction y 2 minus y 1 Over x 2 minus x 1 EndFraction. Substituting the points left parenthesis 0 comma negative 5 right parenthesis and left parenthesis 1 comma negative 1 right parenthesis for left parenthesis x 1 comma y 1 right parenthesis and left parenthesis x 2 comma y 2 right parenthesis, respectively, in the slope formula yields m equals StartFraction left parenthesis negative 1 minus left parenthesis negative 5 right parenthesis right parenthesis Over left parenthesis 1 minus 0 right parenthesis EndFraction, or m equals 4. Substituting 4 for m and negative 5 for b in the equation y equals m x plus b yields y equals 4 x minus 5. \nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}]'::jsonb);
INSERT INTO sat_tests (title, description, test_type, difficulty, length, section, is_official, time_limit_minutes, questions) VALUES ('OpenSAT Math - Normal Set 6','Official-style SAT Math practice (Normal) from OpenSAT — image-free questions only.','math','normal','medium','math',true,38,'[{"id": "opensat-math-mcq-457", "text": "p equals StartFraction k Over 4 j plus 9 EndFraction\nThe given equation relates the distinct positive numbers p, k, and j. Which equation correctly expresses 4 j plus 9 in terms of p and k?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["4 j plus 9 equals StartFraction k Over p EndFraction", "4 j plus 9 equals k p", "4 j plus 9 equals k minus p", "4 j plus 9 equals StartFraction p Over k EndFraction"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. To express 4 j plus 9 in terms of p and k, the given equation must be solved for 4 j plus 9. Since it''s given that j is a positive number, 4 j plus 9 is not equal to zero. Therefore, multiplying both sides of the given equation by 4 j plus 9 yields the equivalent equation p left parenthesis 4 j plus 9 right parenthesis equals k. Since it''s given that p is a positive number, p is not equal to zero. Therefore, dividing each side of the equation p left parenthesis 4 j plus 9 right parenthesis equals k by p yields the equivalent equation 4 j plus 9 equals StartFraction k Over p EndFraction.\nChoice B is incorrect. This equation is equivalent to p equals StartFraction 4 j plus 9 Over k EndFraction.\nChoice C is incorrect. This equation is equivalent to p equals k minus 4 j minus 9.\nChoice D is incorrect. This equation is equivalent to p equals k left parenthesis 4 j plus 9 right parenthesis."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-461", "text": "The area upper A, in square centimeters, of a rectangular cutting board can be represented by the expression w left parenthesis w plus 9 right parenthesis, where w is the width, in centimeters, of the cutting board. Which expression represents the length, in centimeters, of the cutting board?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["w left parenthesis w plus 9 right parenthesis", "w", "9", "left parenthesis w plus 9 right parenthesis"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. It''s given that the expression w left parenthesis w plus 9 right parenthesis represents the area, in square centimeters, of a rectangular cutting board, where w is the width, in centimeters, of the cutting board. The area of a rectangle can be calculated by multiplying its length by its width. It follows that the length, in centimeters, of the cutting board is represented by the expression left parenthesis w plus 9 right parenthesis. \nChoice A is incorrect. This expression represents the area, in square centimeters, of the cutting board, not its length, in centimeters.\nChoice B is incorrect. This expression represents the width, in centimeters, of the cutting board, not its length.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the difference between the length, in centimeters, and the width, in centimeters, of the cutting board, not its length, in centimeters."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-464", "text": "Square X has a side length of 12 centimeters. The perimeter of square Y is 2 times the perimeter of square X. What is the length, in centimeters, of one side of square Y?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["6", "10", "14", "24"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. The perimeter, upper P, of a square can be found using the formula upper P equals 4 s, where s is the length of each side of the square. It''s given that square X has a side length of 12 centimeters. Substituting 12 for s in the formula for the perimeter of a square yields upper P equals 4 left parenthesis 12 right parenthesis, or upper P equals 48. Therefore, the perimeter of square X is 48 centimeters. It\u2019s also given that the perimeter of square Y is 2 times the perimeter of square X. Therefore, the perimeter of square Y is 2 left parenthesis 48 right parenthesis, or 96, centimeters. Substituting 96 for upper P in the formula upper P equals 4 s gives 96 equals 4 s. Dividing both sides of this equation by 4 gives 24 equals s. Therefore, the length of one side of square Y is 24 centimeters.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-465", "text": "A box contains 13 red pens and 37 blue pens. If one of these pens is selected at random, what is the probability of selecting a red pen? (Express your answer as a decimal or fraction, not as a percent.)", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": ".26, 13/50", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "The correct answer is StartFraction 13 Over 50 EndFraction. It''s given that a box contains 13 red pens and 37 blue pens. If one of these pens is selected at random, the probability of selecting a red pen is the number of red pens in the box divided by the number of red and blue pens in the box. The number of red and blue pens in the box is 13 plus 37, or 50. Since there are 13 red pens in the box, it follows that the probability of selecting a red pen is StartFraction 13 Over 50 EndFraction. Note that 13/50 and .26 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-470", "text": "A model predicts that a certain animal weighed 241 pounds when it was born and that the animal gained 3 pounds per day in its first year of life. This model is defined by an equation in the form f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals a plus b x, where f left parenthesis x right parenthesis is the predicted weight, in pounds, of the animal x days after it was born, and a and b are constants. What is the value of a?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "241", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "The correct answer is 241. For a certain animal, it''s given that a model predicts the animal weighed 241 pounds when it was born and gained 3 pounds per day in its first year of life. It''s also given that this model is defined by an equation in the form f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals a plus b x, where f left parenthesis x right parenthesis is the predicted weight, in pounds, of the animal x days after it was born, and a and b are constants. It follows that a represents the predicted weight, in pounds, of the animal when it was born and b represents the predicted rate of weight gain, in pounds per day, in its first year of life. Thus, the value of a is 241."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-472", "text": "A linear model estimates the population of a city from 1991 to 2015. The model estimates the population was 57 thousand in 1991, 224 thousand in 2011, and x thousand in 2015. To the nearest whole number, what is the value of x?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "257", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "The correct answer is 257. It\u2019s given that a linear model estimates the population of a city from 1991 to 2015. Since the population can be estimated using a linear model, it follows that there is a constant rate of change for the model. It\u2019s also given that the model estimates the population was 57 thousand in 1991, 224 thousand in 2011, and x thousand in 2015. The change in the population between 2011 and 1991 is 224 minus 57, or 167, thousand. The change in the number of years between 2011 and 1991 is 2011 minus 1991, or 20, years. Dividing 167 by 20 gives 167 divided by 20, or 8.35, thousand per year. Thus, the change in population per year from 1991 to 2015 estimated by the model is 8.35 thousand. The change in the number of years between 2015 and 2011 is 2015 minus 2011, or 4, years. Multiplying the change in population per year by the change in number of years yields the increase in population from 2011 to 2015 estimated by the model: left parenthesis 8.35 right parenthesis left parenthesis 4 right parenthesis, or 33.4, thousand. Adding the change in population from 2011 to 2015 estimated by the model to the estimated population in 2011 yields the estimated population in 2015. Thus, the estimated population in 2015 is 33.4 plus 224, or 257.4, thousand. Therefore to the nearest whole number, the value of x is 257."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-477", "text": "StartFraction 55 Over x plus 6 EndFraction equals x\nWhat is the positive solution to the given equation?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "5", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "The correct answer is 5. Multiplying both sides of the given equation by x plus 6 results in 55 equals x left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis. Applying the distributive property of multiplication to the right-hand side of this equation results in 55 equals x squared plus 6 x. Subtracting 55 from both sides of this equation results in 0 equals x squared plus 6 x minus 55. The right-hand side of this equation can be rewritten by factoring. The two values that multiply to negative 55 and add to 6 are 11 and negative 5. It follows that the equation 0 equals x squared plus 6 x minus 55 can be rewritten as 0 equals left parenthesis x plus 11 right parenthesis left parenthesis x minus 5 right parenthesis. Setting each factor equal to 0 yields two equations: x plus 11 equals 0 and x minus 5 equals 0. Subtracting 11 from both sides of the equation x plus 11 equals 0 results in x equals negative 11. Adding 5 to both sides of the equation x minus 5 equals 0 results in x equals 5. Therefore, the positive solution to the given equation is 5."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-480", "text": "f left paren