ing the distributive property to the left-hand side of this equation yields 6 t minus 20 equals 40 plus 3 t. Adding 20 to both sides of this equation yields 6 t equals 60 plus 3 t. Subtracting 3 t from both sides of this equation yields 3 t equals 60. Therefore, the value of 3 t is 60."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-487", "text": "Each vertex of a 14-sided polygon is labeled with one of the 14 letters upper A through upper N, with a different letter at each vertex. If one vertex is selected at random, what is the probability that the letter upper D will be at the selected vertex? (Express your answer as a decimal or fraction, not as a percent.)", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": ".0714, 1/14", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "The correct answer is one fourteenth. If one vertex of the polygon is selected at random, the probability that the letter upper D will be at the selected vertex is equal to the number of vertices labeled with the letter upper D divided by the total number of vertices. It''s given that each vertex is labeled with one of the 14 letters upper A through upper N, with a different letter at each vertex. It follows that there is 1 vertex labeled with the letter upper D. It''s also given that the polygon is 14-sided. It follows that there are a total of 14 vertices. Thus, the probability that the letter upper D will be at the selected vertex is one fourteenth. Note that 1/14, .0714, and 0.071 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-488", "text": "The population density of Cedar County is 230 people per square mile. The county has a population of 85,100 people. What is the area, in square miles, of Cedar County?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "370", "difficulty": "normal", "explanation": "The correct answer is 370. It\u2019s given that the population density of Cedar County is 230 people per square mile and the county has a populat