ver 48 EndFraction. It\u2019s given that triangle upper R upper S upper T is similar to triangle upper U upper V upper W, where upper S corresponds to upper V and upper T corresponds to upper W. It follows that upper R corresponds to upper U. Therefore, the hypotenuse of triangle upper U upper V upper W is side upper W upper U, which means tangent upper W equals StartFraction upper U upper V Over upper V upper W EndFraction. Since the lengths of corresponding sides of similar triangles are proportional, StartFraction upper R upper S Over upper S upper T EndFraction equals StartFraction upper U upper V Over upper V upper W EndFraction. Therefore, tangent upper W equals StartFraction upper U upper V Over upper V upper W EndFraction is equivalent to tangent upper W equals StartFraction upper R upper S Over upper S upper T EndFraction, or tangent upper W equals tangent upper T. Thus, tangent upper W equals StartFraction 55 Over 48 EndFraction.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the value of cosine upper W, not tangent upper W.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the value of sine upper W, not tangent upper W.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the value of StartFraction 1 Over tangent upper W EndFraction, not tangent upper W."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-6", "text": "In the xy-plane, a parabola has vertex left parenthesis 9 comma negative 14 right parenthesis and intersects the x-axis at two points. If the equation of the parabola is written in the form y equals a x squared plus b x plus c, where a, b, and c are constants, which of the following could be the value of a plus b plus c?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["negative 23", "negative 19", "negative 14", "negative 12"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. The equation of a parabola in the xy-plane can be written in the form y equals a left parenthesis x minus h right parenthesis squared plus k, where a is a constant and left parenthesis